## Load libraries





::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
suppressPackageStartupMessages({
library(tidyverse)
library(patchwork)
library(DHARMa)
library(glmmTMB)
library(emmeans)
library(gt)
})
```
:::





## Read in data




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
data <- read_csv(here::here("./notebooks/soil_data.csv"))|>
  mutate(date_fct = as.factor(date))  |>
  mutate(elevation = fct_relevel(elevation, c("Upper", "Middle", "Lower", "Riparian"))) |>
  mutate(depth = fct_relevel(depth, c("0-5 cm", "5-10 cm", "0-10 cm")))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr .hidden}

```
Rows: 124 Columns: 11
── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr  (4): flag_location, elevation, depth, watershed
dbl  (5): mass, count, n_m2, mass_m2, mass_n
date (2): date, date_fct

ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
```


:::
:::





## Polymer abundance (0-5 cm)

### Look at data





::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
p1 <- ggplot(data = filter(data, depth == "0-5 cm"), aes(x = elevation, y = n_m2, fill = date_fct)) +
  geom_boxplot(position = position_dodge2(preserve = "single")) +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_fill_viridis_d() +
  labs(y = bquote("Polymer abundance (coatings m"^-2*")"), x = "Slope position")
p1
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](soil_sampling_files/figure-jats/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png)
:::
:::





