### Pairwise comparisons 





::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
em_elev <- emmeans(m1_sqrt, ~ elevation, type = "response") |> 
  regrid() |> 
  contrast(method = "pairwise", adjust = "fdr")  |>
  as.data.frame() |>
  mutate(type = "Slope Position")

em_elev # back transformed
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
        contrast   estimate       SE df    t.ratio    p.value           type
1 Upper - Middle  -18.06178 37.07429 66 -0.4871781 0.62774629 Slope Position
2  Upper - Lower -112.16079 40.56626 66 -2.7648786 0.02212594 Slope Position
3 Middle - Lower  -94.09901 41.20269 66 -2.2838076 0.03841204 Slope Position
```


:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
em_date <- emmeans(m1_sqrt, ~ date_fct, type = "response") |> 
  regrid() |> 
  contrast(method = "pairwise", adjust = "fdr") |>
  as.data.frame() |>
  mutate(type = "Sampling Date") |>
  mutate(contrast = str_remove_all(contrast, "[()]"))

em_date # back transformed
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
                 contrast estimate       SE df  t.ratio      p.value
1 2022-10-21 - 2023-05-11  51.4810 45.17452 66 1.139603 2.585710e-01
2 2022-10-21 - 2023-09-19 241.7163 38.63457 66 6.256476 9.957450e-08
3 2023-05-11 - 2023-09-19 190.2353 36.66474 66 5.188508 3.299117e-06
           type
1 Sampling Date
2 Sampling Date
3 Sampling Date
```


:::

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
pairs <- em_elev |>
  bind_rows(em_date) %>%
  rename("Contrast" = "contrast", "Estimate" = "estimate", "t ratio" = "t.ratio", "p value" = "p.value")
```
:::

::: {#tbl-abundance-posthoc .cell tbl-cap='Results of the post-hoc pairwise comparisons with a Benjamini-Hochberg p value adjustment for differences in the abundance of polymer coatings ($coatings~m^{-2}$) between the three slope positions and sampling dates. Data were square-root transformed prior to analysis and back-transformed to the original scale for reporting.'}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
#| label: tbl-abundance-posthoc
#| tbl-cap: Results of the post-hoc pairwise comparisons with a Benjamini-Hochberg p value adjustment for differences in the abundance of polymer coatings ($coatings~m^{-2}$) between the three slope positions and sampling dates. Data were square-root transformed prior to analysis and back-transformed to the original scale for reporting.

pairs |>
  group_by(type) |>
  gt() |>
  fmt_number(columns = c("Estimate", "SE", "t ratio"), decimal = 2)|>
  fmt_number(columns = c("p value"), decimal = 3)|>
  sub_small_vals(threshold = 0.001) |>
  tab_style(style =  cell_text(weight = "bold", align = "center"), locations =  cells_row_groups()) |>
  tab_options(column_labels.font.weight = "bold")
```

